data.description: Recently renovated with 3 bedrooms, 2 bath and a 1 car garage, With a family room or Bonus room, large privacy fenced yard and a corner lot!  As you walk up to this wonderful home you are greeted by a large front porch area leading to the front door, Flower beds surround the exterior of the home for you to create a beautiful flower garden.  As you enter the front door the spacious living room welcomes you which leads to the kitchen or the secondary bedrooms and main bath.  Both bathrooms are updated and feature beautiful showers.  The kitchen features modern details, NEW floors, fixtures, plenty of beautiful cabinets, a lot of counter space would be great for entertaining, stainless-steel appliances and self-closing drawers. Beyond the kitchen there is a dining room leading to the Master bedroom and the bonus room or family room which ever works for you.    Spacious Master suite features its own bathroom.  Natural sunlight throughout the entire home!  The Home was only lived in a short amount of time after the upgrades.  All updates were done before Current homeowner purchased from what we understand the A/C and electrical panel were updated around 2021. The roof is estimated to be 3.5 years old.  Water heater 2022, Kitchen, Bath, flooring updates, light fixtures and such are also believed to be done in 2022.  Double pain windows unsure of the age. Don’t miss out on this Wonderful Move in Ready home! Great location walking distance to Lakeview Fundamental Elementary School, I-275 is about 3 minutes away, Under 10-minute drive in regular traffic to Downtown St Pete, St. Pete's Grand Central District, Warehouse Art's District, Tropicana Field, Pinellas Trail Access St. Pete pier, Dali museum and many other attractions. Schedule your in-person tour ASAP before its gone.  Be sure to check out the Virtual Walk Through!
